				<h3>Re: Transmission built in.</h3>
				<div class="date"><img src="./styles/absolution/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />Posted: <strong>Sat Feb 05, 2011 11:00 am</strong></div>
				<div class="author">by <strong>Roby</strong></div>
				<div class="content"><![if !IE]><div class="bubble"></div><![endif]><blockquote><div><cite>earthdan wrote:</cite><![if !IE]><div class="bubble"></div><![endif]><blockquote><div><cite>Roby wrote:</cite><![if !IE]><div class="bubble"></div><![endif]><blockquote><div><cite>earthdan wrote:</cite>I get the unspecified error after I check the box &quot;enable torrents&quot;, enter in my username and password to get to the transmission page, and then click save. It goes to a warning page saying something about the legality of torrents etc., then I click ok, and then it thinks for a few seconds and spits out the error. Super annoying!</div></blockquote><br /><br />Yeah, it's a bug.  We'll have it fixed for 2.5.1 .  What happen is you have 2 locales in your branding.conf.  So 1, fix your locale (remove one and keep the correct one).  Secondly, find the branding.conf.xx for your branding and copy the dirTorrentDownloads= in your branding.conf.  Third, create a symlink in /var/axentra/ like this:<br /><br />lrwxrwxrwx 1 root   root    31 Jan 21 20:10 torrentDir -&gt; /home/0common/Torrent Downloads .  It's ok that /home/0common/Torrent Downloads doesn't exist, it will get created when you enable torrents.<br /><br />Then Enable torrent.<br /><br />Cheers,<br />Roby!</div></blockquote><br /><br /><br />Hi Roby,<br /><br />It appears that when I open the branding.conf I see this line :<br />locales=en_US fr_FR es_ES nl_NL de_DE it_IT sv_SE da_DK nb_NO pt_PT pt_BR zh_CN zh_TW ru_RU ko_KR ja_JP<br />and this line:<br />currentLocale=en-US<br /><br />When I open branding.conf.en-US I see a bunch of dir&quot;...&quot; including dirTorrentDownloads=Torrent Downloads<br /><br />So which one should I delete?<br /><br />Also, I am having trouble using that lrwxrwxrwx, as terminal does not recognize that command. However, in the branding.conf file it looks like my torrent directory is already set:<br />dirTorrentDownloads=Torrent Downloads<br /><br />This makes sense to me because I had transmission going before the firmware update and set to download to that directory. One thing that I should mention that might be playing a part in my problems is that there is a pesky file in the Torrent Downloads folder that cannot be deleted at all. It was part of a torrent I was running but for some reason did not finish and now it thinks it is in use and can't be deleted.<br /><br />Thanks for your help!<br /><br />cheers,<br />Dan</div></blockquote><br /><br />ok, by the sounds of your config files, you're not affected by the bug I mentioned (few are).  What are your permissions on the /home/0common/Torrent Downloads directory?<br /><br />Cheers,<br />Roby!</div>
