				<h3>Re: Transmission built in.</h3>
				<div class="date"><img src="./styles/absolution/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />Posted: <strong>Sat Feb 12, 2011 11:32 am</strong></div>
				<div class="author">by <strong>Johan</strong></div>
				<div class="content">Just found out how to change the Torrent Download directory to a custom one.<br />I don't want to have the Torrent Downloads in the GoFlex Home Public dir. But I just managed to move it to the the GoFlex Home Personal/Torrent Download dir for a certain user that I created.<br /><br />To do it. <br />Simply remove the symbolic link /var/axentra/torrentDir and create a new link to the directory of your choice. <br />Just make sure to set ownership apache:users for the directory.<br /><br /><br />@Dan, this is probably not the problem but just in case. Did you login with an admin account over ssh before using sudo -E -s. It seems that only users with admin rights can become root using the sudo -E -s. And you need to be root to remove a directory using rm -r<br /><br />/Johan</div>
			</div>
